---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ImgPlaceholder from '../../components/ImgPlaceholder.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = [
    { slug:'find-suppliers-1688',    title:'How to Find Reliable Suppliers on 1688 Without Speaking Chinese', cat:'Sourcing Guide', time:'5 min', date:'2024-11-12', desc:'Step-by-step guide to China\'s largest B2B platform.', seed:601, hint:'建议：1688平台截图 / 义乌商城，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>1688.com is China's largest domestic wholesale marketplace — run by Alibaba but used almost exclusively by Chinese buyers. Prices are dramatically lower than Alibaba.com because there's no English-language premium.</p><h2>Step 1: Use Google Translate's camera mode</h2><p>Install Google Translate on your phone and use the camera feature to translate 1688's interface in real time. It gets you 80% of the way there.</p><h2>Step 2: Search with product images</h2><p>1688 has powerful image search. Upload a photo or screenshot of any product and instantly see dozens of Chinese suppliers producing the exact item.</p><h2>Step 3: Evaluate by transaction volume</h2><p>Look for sellers with high transaction counts (成交量) and strong reviews. 10,000+ transactions signals a legitimate, reliable operation.</p><h2>Step 4: Let CrossPals handle communication</h2><p>Once you've identified a promising supplier, send us the link. We'll contact them in Chinese, verify pricing and MOQs, and confirm they're legitimate — before you commit a dollar.</p><p>Ready to start? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> with your 1688 link.</p>` },
    { slug:'air-vs-sea-freight',     title:'Air vs Sea Freight: Which Should You Choose for Your First Order?', cat:'Shipping', time:'4 min', date:'2024-10-28', desc:'Cost-benefit breakdown for first-time importers.', seed:602, hint:'建议：货运飞机 / 集装箱港口，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>The question every first-time importer asks: air or sea? The answer depends on your order value, weight, urgency, and destination.</p><h2>Air Freight</h2><p>Typically 5–10 days, costing $5–$15 per kilogram. Ideal for small, high-value orders — electronics, jewelry, accessories.</p><h2>Sea Freight (LCL)</h2><p>20–40 days, costing $1–$3 per kilogram. LCL lets you share a container with other importers. Best for heavy or bulky goods over 200kg.</p><h2>Our Rule of Thumb</h2><p><strong>Under $1,000:</strong> Express courier (DHL, FedEx).<br/><strong>$1,000–$5,000:</strong> Air freight depending on weight.<br/><strong>Over $5,000 with heavy goods:</strong> Sea freight LCL.</p><p>Have a specific order? <a href="/contact">Ask us</a> and we'll calculate the exact shipping cost.</p>` },
    { slug:'cheap-china-products',   title:'5 Products That Are Cheaper in China and Sell Well Everywhere', cat:'Business Tips', time:'6 min', date:'2024-10-05', desc:'Product ideas with proven margins across multiple markets.', seed:603, hint:'建议：热销商品陈列 / 产品展示，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>Not every product category has dramatic price advantages from China. But these five consistently offer strong margins for import entrepreneurs.</p><h2>1. Phone Accessories</h2><p>China produces 90%+ of global phone accessories. Cases, chargers, screen protectors. Retail margin potential: 200–400%.</p><h2>2. Fashion Jewelry</h2><p>Yiwu is the world's largest small commodity market. Pieces you buy for $0.50–$2 commonly retail for $8–$25 in Western and African markets.</p><h2>3. Home Organization & Kitchen</h2><p>Storage containers, silicone kitchenware, space-saving gadgets. High demand across all markets.</p><h2>4. Beauty Tools</h2><p>Lash kits, facial rollers, hair tools. Low weight means low shipping costs.</p><h2>5. Custom Activewear</h2><p>China produces most of the world's activewear. Custom logo minimums as low as 50–100 pieces.</p><p><a href="/contact">Tell us which category interests you</a> — we'll find the best current suppliers.</p>` },
    { slug:'avoid-alibaba-scams',    title:'How to Avoid the 7 Most Common Alibaba Scams', cat:'Safety', time:'7 min', date:'2024-09-20', desc:'Protect your money by learning the red flags experienced importers watch for.', seed:604, hint:'建议：合同/警示/安全场景，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>Alibaba is used by millions of legitimate businesses worldwide. But it also hosts middlemen, fraudsters, and low-quality operators.</p><h2>1. The Too-Good-to-Be-True Price</h2><p>If a supplier's price is 30–50% below every other listing, something is wrong. Use it as reference only.</p><h2>2. Moving Off Platform</h2><p>A supplier who asks to negotiate on WhatsApp bypasses Trade Assurance. Never pay outside the platform on a first order.</p><h2>3. Sample Bait-and-Switch</h2><p>Excellent sample, terrible bulk order. Always specify bulk goods must match the approved sample — and inspect before releasing payment.</p><h2>4. Fake Gold Supplier Badges</h2><p>Gold Supplier status just means they paid for a subscription. Look at transaction history and reviews instead.</p><h2>5. Inflated Shipping Quotes</h2><p>Some suppliers make hidden margin on shipping. Always get an independent freight quote to compare.</p><h2>6. The Deposit Disappearance</h2><p>Never pay 100% upfront to a new supplier. Standard terms: 30% deposit, 70% after inspection.</p><h2>7. Counterfeit Certificates</h2><p>CE, ISO certificates are easy to fake. Ask for the certificate number and verify — or let CrossPals verify for you.</p>` },
    { slug:'custom-packaging-guide', title:'Custom Packaging from China: A Beginner\'s Complete Guide', cat:'Branding', time:'5 min', date:'2024-09-08', desc:'Your logo on boxes, bags, and labels — MOQs, costs, and lead times.', seed:605, hint:'建议：定制包装盒 / 品牌印刷 / 开箱展示，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>Custom packaging is one of the fastest ways to make your product look like a real brand. China makes it surprisingly affordable — even for small first orders.</p><h2>Types of Custom Packaging</h2><p><strong>Printed poly bags</strong> (MOQ: 500–1,000 pcs): cheapest entry point.<br/><strong>Custom boxes</strong> (MOQ: 500–2,000 pcs): premium look and feel.<br/><strong>Hang tags & inserts</strong>: often orderable from 200 pcs.</p><h2>What You Need to Provide</h2><p>Your logo in vector format (AI or EPS), brand colors in CMYK, product dimensions, and any regulatory text.</p><h2>Lead Times</h2><p>Standard packaging: 7–15 days after artwork approval. Complex printing: 15–25 days.</p><h2>Cost Ranges</h2><p>Simple poly bag with logo: $0.05–$0.20 each at 1,000 pcs.<br/>Kraft box with full-color print: $0.30–$1.50 each at 1,000 pcs.<br/>Premium rigid box: $1.50–$5.00 each at 500 pcs.</p><p>Need custom packaging? <a href="/contact">Tell us your requirements</a>.</p>` },
    { slug:'payment-methods-suppliers', title:'The Safest Ways to Pay Chinese Suppliers', cat:'Payments', time:'4 min', date:'2024-08-22', desc:'From Trade Assurance to wire transfers — protecting your money.', seed:606, hint:'建议：网上支付/银行/合同场景，宽幅横向',
      body:`<p>Paying a supplier in China for the first time can feel nerve-wracking. Here are the most common payment methods, ranked safest to riskiest.</p><h2>1. Alibaba Trade Assurance (Safest)</h2><p>For Alibaba orders, Trade Assurance provides buyer protection. If goods don't match specs, Alibaba investigates and may refund you. Always use it for first orders.</p><h2>2. PayPal (Good for Samples)</h2><p>PayPal's buyer protection is useful for sample payments under $500. Most suppliers add a 3–5% surcharge.</p><h2>3. Letter of Credit</h2><p>The bank only releases funds when shipping documents are verified. Costs $200–$500 to set up but highly secure for orders over $10,000.</p><h2>4. T/T Wire Transfer (Use Carefully)</h2><p>The most common method for established relationships. Standard terms: 30% deposit T/T, 70% balance before shipment after QC. Never pay 100% upfront.</p><h2>5. Western Union / MoneyGram (Avoid)</h2><p>Zero buyer protection. Only appropriate with suppliers you've worked with for years.</p><p>CrossPals handles payments to suppliers on your behalf — your money is protected through our established payment infrastructure.</p>` },
  ];
  return posts.map(p => ({ params:{ slug:p.slug }, props:{ post:p } }));
}

const { post } = Astro.props;
---
<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.desc}>

  <!-- Article hero with full-width cover image -->
  <!-- 📸 SLOT O: 文章头图 — 建议：与文章主题紧密相关的横向宽图 16:6 -->
  <div class="article-cover" style="padding-top:74px;">
    <ImgPlaceholder
      seed={post.seed} width={1400} height={525} ratio="16/6"
      alt={post.title}
      hint={post.hint ?? '建议：与文章主题相关的横向宽图'}
    />
  </div>

  <header class="article-hdr">
    <div class="container article-hdr__inner">
      <a href="/blog" class="back">← Back to Blog</a>
      <span class="article-cat">{post.cat}</span>
      <h1>{post.title}</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <time>{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US',{month:'long',day:'numeric',year:'numeric'})}</time>
        <span>·</span><span>{post.time} read</span>
        <span>·</span><span>CrossPals Team</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container article-grid">
      <div class="prose reveal" set:html={post.body} />

      <aside class="article-aside reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="aside-cta">
          <p class="overline">Need Help?</p>
          <h4>Let CrossPals Find Your Suppliers</h4>
          <p>Tell us your requirements. Supplier options in 48 hours.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Free Quote <svg class="arrow-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
        </div>
        <nav class="aside-nav">
          <p class="overline">Explore</p>
          <a href="/services">Our Services →</a>
          <a href="/about">About CrossPals →</a>
          <a href="/blog">All Articles →</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-cover :global(.img-ph){border-radius:0;}
  .article-cover :global(.img-ph__wrap){border-radius:0;}
  .article-hdr{background:var(--warm-100);padding:var(--s7) 0 var(--s6);border-bottom:1px solid var(--warm-200);}
  .article-hdr__inner{max-width:820px;}
  .back{display:inline-block;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;font-family:var(--font-mono);color:var(--text-body);text-decoration:none;margin-bottom:var(--s4);transition:color var(--t-fast);letter-spacing:0.04em;}
  .back:hover{color:var(--avo-700);}
  .article-cat{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--avo-600);display:block;margin-bottom:var(--s3);}
  .article-hdr h1{margin-bottom:var(--s4);max-width:760px;}
  .article-meta{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--s3);font-size:12px;color:var(--warm-400);font-family:var(--font-mono);}
  .article-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 300px;gap:var(--s8);align-items:start;}
  .prose{font-size:17px;line-height:1.85;color:var(--text-body);max-width:660px;}
  .prose :global(p){margin-bottom:var(--s5);}
  .prose :global(h2){font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:clamp(22px,2.5vw,28px);color:var(--warm-950);margin:var(--s8) 0 var(--s4);padding-top:var(--s6);border-top:2px solid var(--warm-200);}
  .prose :global(h2:first-child){margin-top:0;border-top:none;padding-top:0;}
  .prose :global(strong){color:var(--warm-950);}
  .prose :global(a){color:var(--avo-700);font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;text-decoration-color:var(--avo-200);}
  .article-aside{position:sticky;top:90px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--s5);}
  .aside-cta{background:var(--avo-700);border-radius:var(--r3);padding:var(--s6);color:#fff;}
  .aside-cta .overline{color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);margin-bottom:var(--s3);}
  .aside-cta h4{color:#fff;font-size:17px;margin-bottom:var(--s3);}
  .aside-cta>p{font-size:14px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.6);}
  .aside-nav{background:var(--warm-100);border:1px solid var(--warm-200);border-radius:var(--r3);padding:var(--s5);display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--s3);}
  .aside-nav .overline{margin-bottom:var(--s2);}
  .aside-nav a{font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--avo-700);text-decoration:none;transition:color var(--t-fast);}
  .aside-nav a:hover{color:var(--avo-500);}
  @media(max-width:860px){.article-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.article-aside{position:static}}
</style>
